. I‚Äôve become more comfortable with entering a space with vulnerability and openness as a co-learner, ready to have my understandings and views shifted and expanded, if not transformed. I‚Äôve been spending the past 6 weeks or so hanging out with Gen Zers as part of my pilot study and they‚Äôve introduced me to hidden worlds that I could only have dreamed of back in my AOL dial-up years. They‚Äôre brilliant in their own ways and so eager to share if only we cared to ask. I‚Äôve been stuck with my blog, not sure where to take it. I haven‚Äôt written for months and even here, I‚Äôve barely posted. I‚Äôm hoping to feel my way into being a writer again. And I have a feeling my students, study participants, colleagues, and teachers will support me on this journey of writing my world. This photo was taken a week ago in my favorite park. I was admiring the majestic trees. 
